[[File:Konojinja940.jpg|thumb|To Shrine torii and shrine name marker]]

'''Tono Shrine''' (とのじんじゃ) is a shrine in {{ill|lt=Toyooka|Q696388|WD=Q696388|1=Toyooka, Hyōgo}}, {{ill|lt=Hyōgo Prefecture|Q130290|WD=Q130290|1=Hyōgo Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=myōjin taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}), its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}, and it is a designated shrine for offerings of sacred food and silk.

=== Overview ===
An ancient shrine counted as one of the ten myōjin taisha in Tajima Province. Its enshrined deity Ōtohime-no-Mikoto is also called Okutsu-hime-no-Kami, a deity governing hearths.

=== Enshrined deity ===
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōtohime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== History ===
"Shoku Nihon Kōki," Jōwa 9, 10th month, day 15 (842)

In Tajima Province, five deities of Keta District and Kinosaki District - Yama deity, Thunder deity, To deity, [木蜀]椒 deity, and Sea deity - were all entered among official shrines.

"Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku," Jōgan 10, 12th month, day 27 (868)

Bestowed ranks: In Tajima Province, Izushi and Awaga deities were given Senior Fifth Rank Lower; Yama, To, Thunder, [木蜀]椒, and Sea deities were given Senior Fifth Rank Upper.

"Engishiki" 3 (Rinji-sai), myōjin festival article [28]
Awaga Shrine one seat. Yabu Shrine two seats. Izushi Shrine eight seats.
Yama Shrine one seat. To Shrine one seat. Thunder Shrine one seat.
[木蜀]椒 Shrine one seat. Sea Shrine one seat.
All above in Tajima Province.

=== About official shrines of Tajima Province ===
"Engishiki" 3 (Rinji-sai), myōjin festival article [28]

Myōjin festival, 285 seats. Awaga Shrine one seat. Yabu Shrine two seats. Izushi Shrine eight seats.
Yama Shrine one seat. To Shrine one seat. Thunder Shrine one seat.
[木蜀]椒 Shrine one seat. Sea Shrine one seat. All above in Tajima Province.

=== Sessha and massha ===
Itsukushima Shrine and Nagusa Shrine

